article.headline: James Madison 85, Radford 81
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Kyle Swanston scored 23 points and James Madison defeated Radford 85-81 on Sunday. Juwann James added 19 points on 8-of-10 shooting for the Dukes (5-4) and Devon Moore had 10 points and seven assists. James led the Dukes' second unit, which scored 24 points, compared to two by Radford's bench. Four players scored in double figures for the Highlanders (3-6) as Artsiom Parakhouski and Martell McDuffy led the way with 23 and 20, respectively. Amir Johnson chipped in 16 points and 10 assists and Kenny Thomas added 12 points. Radford led 43-37 at halftime, but the Dukes shot 65.4 percent from the field (17 of 26) and 91.7 percent (11 of 12) from the free-throw line in the second half.
